{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012TjJv3vjQ8J52SYUawKb1P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EwyzRB8kDQBQzKLUMLTp8Z","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Session retrospective","prompt":"Run a session retrospective for the codeharness sprint.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to get token consumption data, then read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md`.\n\nThis is session 44. It was a no-op session — the sprint is complete (74/74 stories done across 17 epics). The only work done was fixing Ralph state corruption for the 28th time: stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were reverted to `review` by Ralph's stale in-memory state, and phantom story `1-1-foo` reappeared.\n\nKey context:\n- Sessions 17-44 have ALL been no-op state corruption fixes\n- Ralph keeps overwriting sprint-state.json with stale in-memory state\n- The `registerStory` guard deployed in session 22 prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent status reversion\n- Each no-op session wastes API tokens fixing the same 4 stories\n\nWrite the retrospective to `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`. If it already exists, append with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nInclude:\n1. Session summary — no-op, state corruption fix #28\n2. Issues analysis — the Ralph state corruption is the only issue, 28 occurrences\n3. Cost analysis — run `codeharness stats --save` and read the cost report\n4. What went well — efficient fix (~10 tool calls)\n5. What went wrong — Ralph still corrupting state after 28 sessions\n6. Lessons learned — Ralph needs to be killed or its state write path needs to be fixed\n7. Action items — kill Ralph process, fix the root cause\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":994,"cache_read_input_tokens":49112,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":994},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a12053af-fcbc-4eef-b6c9-cca47dbf3a5b","uuid":"40dc3384-071f-46a7-a1f1-4b89f7c56200"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a0e64338ab5904f6c","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EwyzRB8kDQBQzKLUMLTp8Z","description":"Session retrospective","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Run a session retrospective for the codeharness sprint.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\nCost report: Run `codeharness stats --save` to get token consumption data, then read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md`.\n\nThis is session 44. It was a no-op session — the sprint is complete (74/74 stories done across 17 epics). The only work done was fixing Ralph state corruption for the 28th time: stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 were reverted to `review` by Ralph's stale in-memory state, and phantom story `1-1-foo` reappeared.\n\nKey context:\n- Sessions 17-44 have ALL been no-op state corruption fixes\n- Ralph keeps overwriting sprint-state.json with stale in-memory state\n- The `registerStory` guard deployed in session 22 prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent status reversion\n- Each no-op session wastes API tokens fixing the same 4 stories\n\nWrite the retrospective to `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`. If it already exists, append with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nInclude:\n1. Session summary — no-op, state corruption fix #28\n2. Issues analysis — the Ralph state corruption is the only issue, 28 occurrences\n3. Cost analysis — run `codeharness stats --save` and read the cost report\n4. What went well — efficient fix (~10 tool calls)\n5. What went wrong — Ralph still corrupting state after 28 sessions\n6. Lessons learned — Ralph needs to be killed or its state write path needs to be fixed\n7. Action items — kill Ralph process, fix the root cause\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","uuid":"4dad3363-0419-4b0b-ace5-6d667504c6df","session_id":"a12053af-fcbc-4eef-b6c9-cca47dbf3a5b"}
